title: ENGIE :  Deutsche Bank cuts its price target
full_text: On Friday, Deutsche Bank cut its price target for Engie from 17 to 16.5 euros, believing that the nuclear agreement reached with the Belgian government came at a cost.As a reminder, the energy group announced yesterday that it had agreed with the Belgian government to extend the lifespan of two of its nuclear power plants, an agreement that was accompanied by the setting of a lump sum for future waste treatment costs.This agreement eliminates a major risk for the stock, but it also comes at a significant premium to the book value of its nuclear provisions", the broker points out.The increase in these commitments will correspond to an amount of around 4.5 billion euros (or 1.9 euros per share), much higher than the two billion euros that the broker was anticipating.DB nevertheless maintains its buy recommendation on the share.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: RENAULT  :  Stifel confirms its Buy rating on the share
full_text: Stifel maintains its Buy rating on Renault shares, with an unchanged target price of 48 euros. While the Group has raised its forecasts for the year, the analyst believes that operating income should be boosted by "at least a quarter" thanks to the quality of sales (volume/price/mix) and a less unfavorable cost base (raw materials/transportation/energy/supplier remuneration). As a result, 'Renault's profitability could reach new heights in 2023, surpassing the previous record set in... 1999 (before the Nissan era)', argues Stifel.Le Losange now anticipates: (1) a Group margin of between 7% and 8% (compared with 6% or more previously) and (2) automotive operating FCF of over E2.5 billion (compared with over E2 billion previously).According to Stifel, given the pace of product launches in 2024 (14 new cars) and 2025 (five new cars), as well as work on costs, 'forward financial statements could prove even more attractive than in 2023'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Societe Generale: the stock benefits from an upgrade in opinion
full_text: On Friday, Societe Generale was the biggest riser on the Paris Bourse's CAC 40 index, after Deutsche Bank upgraded its recommendation on the stock to "buy".At around 2:15 pm, the French banking group's shares gained nearly 3%, while the CAC 40 index advanced by 1%.Deutsche Bank announced this morning that it had upgraded its recommendation on the stock from "hold" to "buy", with a price target of 34 euros, indicating a potential appreciation of 45%.The intermediary justifies its decision by the fact that several favorable elements are on the horizon for the establishment up to 2024, starting with a recovery in net interest income (NII) from the retail banking division in France.The analyst also points to the forthcoming materialization of cost reductions resulting from the restructuring of the branch network, as well as the positive effects of the merger between ALD and LeasePlan."The solid quality of its assets, the correct level of its available capital and return on capital, and a cheap valuation complete this investment case", adds DB.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JPMorgan raises target for Siemens to 200 euros - 'Overweight'
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan raised its price target for Siemens from 188 to 200 euros ahead of quarterly results and left its rating at "Overweight." After a string of excellent quarters, momentum slowed somewhat in the third fiscal quarter, analyst Andrew Wilson wrote in an outlook report available Friday. He said this was due to a stronger-than-expected normalization in Digital Industries and the impact of challenges announced by Siemens Energy. He justified the new price target by citing his updated forecasts and shifting the valuation horizon into the future./edh/tih  Publication of the original study: 29.06.2023 / 19:47 / BST First disclosure of the original study: 30.06.2023 / 00:25 / BST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Real estate stocks recover after weak first half - LEG helps
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Real estate stocks rallied Friday at the end of a weak first half. The Stoxx Europe 600 Real Estate sector index rebounded from its low since October 2022, but is still down nearly 12 percent in 2023.      It continues to suffer from the interest rate hike cycle to combat high inflation and falling real estate valuations. Only the commodities sector, which is particularly sensitive to the economy, has been weaker this year.      However, sentiment was somewhat improved on the last trading day in June by news from LEG Immobilien. The Düsseldorf-based company had raised its forecasts for 2023 the previous evening. In particular, the now higher expected rental growth was welcomed by the market.      The shares of LEG gained up to 7.5 percent and thus curbed their half-year loss to 11 percent. Vonovia also made clear gains in the Dax, but remains the second-weakest stock in the leading index in the first half of the year, down 19 percent. In the SDax, Patrizia was the best performer on Friday, gaining around four and a half percent./ag/ajx/stk

title: SOCIÉTÉ GÉNÉRALE :  Deutsche Bank upgrades its recommendation to 'buy
full_text: Deutsche Bank announced on Friday that it had upgraded its recommendation on Societe Generale from 'hold' to 'buy', believing that the French banking group was 'on the cusp of a turnaround'.The research firm believes that several favorable elements are on the horizon for the bank by 2024, starting with a recovery in net interest income (NII) in its French retail banking division.The analyst also points to the imminent materialization of cost reductions resulting from the restructuring of the branch network, as well as the positive effects of the merger between ALD and LeasePlan.The solid quality of its assets, the correct level of available capital and return on capital, and a cheap valuation complete this investment case," adds DB.In its note, Deutsche Bank says it does not anticipate any major strategic changes with the arrival of the new CEO, but stresses that certain initiatives, such as the disposal of certain African subsidiaries, could be well received by the market.Its unchanged price target of 34 euros shows a potential upside of 45%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Deutsche Bank Research starts Nordex with 'Buy' - Target 17 Euro
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Deutsche Bank Research has added a "Buy" rating and a target price of 17 euros to Nordex. The onshore wind turbine business looks compelling, as Nordex is well positioned in most key regions and has posted impressive share gains recently, analyst John Kim wrote in a research note issued Friday. The market is still failing to recognize the company's margin potential, easing cost pressures, reduction in low-margin order backlog and lower risk profile or improved balance sheet, he added./edh/tih  Publication of the original study: 06/30/2023 / Time not specified in study / GMT First disclosure of original study: 30.06.2023 / 04:01 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: RENAULT :  Oddo BHF raises its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Renault shares, with a price target raised from 55 to 60 euros. Yesterday, Renault announced an upward revision of its outlook for 2023. According to Oddo BHF, these elements 'confirm that the fears were exaggerated and that the levers for improvement for the automaker remain largely underestimated, as evidenced by the magnitude of the expected upward revisions (>25% at EBIT 2023 level for the consensus).'The analyst finds himself confirmed in his idea that the automaker is 'well ahead of its objectives' and that 'the best is yet to come, even though the product offensive is still in its early stages'. What's more, "the CFO confirmed that the order book remains very solid (record level still anticipated at the end of June, 3-4 months) and also offers certainty for the first part of 2024", concludes the broker. full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Engie shares, with a price target reduced from 19 to 18.5 euros. The analyst reports that Engie and the Belgian government have reached an agreement for the extension of 2 nuclear reactors for a further 10 years and, above all, for the transfer of the long-term nuclear waste management risk.The agreement is based on the fixing of a lump sum of E15 billion.'In the medium term, the agreement will free up the assets held by Electrabel, which were guaranteed to the Belgian state to cover nuclear liabilities', stresses Oddo BHF. title: VIVENDI :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation ahead of earnings results
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Vivendi shares, with an unchanged target price of 13 euros. While Vivendi will publish its Q1 results on July 27, Oddo BHF anticipates slight group-wide sales growth in Q2 (+2%).  EBITA should rise by 21%, notably due to a strong increase in Lagardère's contribution", according to the analyst, who expects a "reassuring" publication, with "improved results from most entities".Oddo BHF expects H1 sales of 4650 ME, with EBITA of 501 ME (376 ME, excluding contributions from UMG and Lagardère), compared with 412 ME last year. The brokerage is slightly lowering its full-year expectations, with EBITA of 1,019 ME for 2023 versus 1,039 ME previously.  We don't expect any strategic changes with these results. However, it will be interesting to follow the company's message on share buybacks', says the analyst. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Carrefour: share price rises, Morgan Stanley in support
full_text: Carrefour's shares rose for the fourth consecutive session on the Paris Bourse on Wednesday, buoyed by a positive recommendation from analysts at Morgan Stanley.At around 12:10 pm, the French retail giant's shares climbed 3%, topping the CAC 40 and SBF 120 indices, bringing their gains over the past week to over 6%.The stock benefited from a positive recommendation from Morgan Stanley, who advised investors to "overweight" the stock, with a target price of 21 euros.The research firm considers that strategic changes are taking place at the retailer, offering an interesting window of opportunity for the stock, especially since, with a PER of 7.8x, the current valuation does not take into account the group's potential, nor the prospect of increased share buybacks, it continues.Indeed, Morgan Stanley expects Carrefour to redistribute to its shareholders cash representing more than 35% of its market capitalization over the next three years.This makes the stock its 'top pick' within the European retail sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

full_text: AlphaValue on Wednesday renewed its 'accumulate' recommendation and 587 euro price target on Kering, questioning whether fragrances could be the luxury group's next growth driver.These comments come as Kering Beauté last week reached an agreement to acquire 100% of Creed from BlackRock, an all-cash transaction.In a note, AlphaValue points out that Creed is one of the world's most popular niche and prestige fragrance brands, with annual sales of 250 million euros and an operating margin deemed 'attractive'.From the research firm's point of view, this acquisition confirms Kering's ambitions in the fast-growing luxury beauty segment, a step in the right direction following the appointment earlier this year of a former Estée Lauder executive, Raffaella Cornaggia, as Managing Director of Kering Beauté.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: BioMérieux: share price up, broker raises his recommendation
full_text: bioMérieux gained almost 2% on the Paris stock exchange after Oddo BHF raised its recommendation on the stock from 'neutral' to 'outperform', and included it in its 'European midcap list', with a price target maintained at 105 euros, in view of the recent downturn in the share price, although visibility seems good.bioMérieux should benefit from several growth opportunities in the short and medium term", believes the analyst, who cites in particular its new lowplex diagnostic systems, SpotFire, launched last March in the United States.Assuming a slowdown in sales of respiratory panels, Oddo BHF expects consolidated sales to grow by +4% to +6% at constant exchange rates and scope of consolidation (or 8-10% excluding respiratory panels linked to Covid) in 2023.The stock is trading at 16 times 12-month EBIT, below its 10-year average of 19 times, despite an industry position that has never looked so favorable", he judges, pointing out, among other things, higher margins than before Covid. title: Casino: share price falls, broker lowers target
full_text: Casino lost almost 2% in Paris this morning, as Oddo BHF confirmed its 'underperform' rating on the stock, with a target price significantly reduced from 6.4 euros to 1 euro, anticipating 'a calamitous 2023... and a major restructuring'.The analyst reports that the figures presented yesterday by Casino in its slideshow reflect the effect of a marked drop in prices since the beginning of March, without compensating for this with an equally marked increase in customer traffic and purchases.The Group says it expects positive sales growth in Q4 2023 for supermarkets and by H1 2024 for hypermarkets.In this context, EBITDA 2023 after rent is expected at ME 439 (Oddo BHF had forecast ME 775 in its model) and EBITDA 2024 after rent is expected at ME 656.All the details of the restructuring have not yet been finalized, but whatever the scenario, the central assumption is that current shareholders will be massively diluted. We are therefore adjusting our OC to 1.0 E vs. 6.4 E, which is a best-case scenario, pending further visibility on the restructuring parameters', concludes the broker. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: RENAULT :  Stifel remains Buy with Alpine ambitions
full_text: On Tuesday, Stifel renewed its Buy recommendation and its target price of 48 euros for Renault, following yesterday's presentation of the development plan for Alpine, the automaker's sports car brand.In addition to Ampere's forthcoming launch and possible IPO, which is generating a great deal of interest among investors following the diamond group, yesterday's event provided a refreshing look at Alpine, which Renault hopes to move from a niche segment to a more global market, explains the broker.For the group, Alpine could become the Trojan horse enabling it to enter the US market (via distribution agreements) and make a comeback in China, it argues.And while Stifel believes that it's still far too early to assign tangible value to these projects, he believes that the eventual successful launches of the A290, a modernized Renault 5, and the c-XO GT crossover - in 2024 and then 2025 - could highlight the company's value-creation potential.In the shorter term, however, the market's attention should be focused on the publication of half-yearly results in July, a date for which forecasts are constantly being revised upwards, he concludes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JPMorgan leaves Rheinmetall at 'Overweight' - Target 310 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan left its rating on Rheinmetall at "Overweight" with a price target of 310 euros. Even if the war in Ukraine comes to an end, Europe is still only at the beginning of a five- to 10-year investment cycle in armaments, analyst David Perry wrote in an industry report available Tuesday. That also applies to Far Eastern nations such as Japan and Australia, he said. And the orders already completed alone point to robust multi-year growth for some major European defense groups, he added. Among these, Perry singled out BAE Systems, Rheinmetall and Thales./bek/tih  Original study publication date: 26.06.2023 / 20:04 / BST First disclosure of original study: 27.06.2023 / 00:15 / BST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: CASINO :  restructuring expected, Oddo BHF lowers its target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'underperform' rating on Casino shares, with a price target significantly reduced from 6.4 euros to 1 euro, anticipating 'a calamitous 2023... and a major restructuring'. The analyst reports that the figures presented yesterday by Casino in its slideshow reflect the effect of a marked drop in prices since the beginning of March, without compensating for this with an equally marked increase in customer traffic and purchases. The Group expects positive sales growth in Q4 2023 for supermarkets and by H1 2024 for hypermarkets. In this context, EBITDA 2023 after rent is expected at 439 ME (Oddo BHF had forecast 775 ME in its model) and EBITDA 2024 after rent is expected at 656 ME.'All the details of the restructuring have not been finalized, but whatever the scenario, the central assumption is that of massive dilution of current shareholders. We are therefore adjusting our OC to 1.0 E vs. 6.4 E, which is a best-case scenario, pending further visibility on the restructuring parameters', concludes the broker. title: Siemens Energy continues to suffer from high uncertainty
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Siemens Energy shares continued their downward slide on Monday. After the withdrawal of annual targets late Thursday evening, the shares of the power engineering group have since fallen by a total of more than 40 percent. At less than 14 euros, they hit another low since November 2022.       "The predictability is too poor," was how Vivek Midha from Citigroup justified the withdrawal of his previous buy recommendation. The assessment of the situation at the problem child, the Spanish subsidiary Siemens Gamesa, had changed fundamentally compared to his "Buy" rating in May, Midha said. Siemens Energy had reported on Thursday significantly increased failure rates for wind turbine components and that planned improvements in productivity are not materializing to the extent previously expected.       Midha currently sees an enormously wide corridor between the optimal case and the worst case: if Siemens Energy were to really get to grips with the credibility problem, the shares could more than double very quickly, the expert says. He then puts a fair value of 34 euros in prospect. However, if the problems continue to make waves, he even considers a low of 11 euros to be possible.      The experts at Jefferies and DZ Bank also lowered their thumbs at the start of the week and lifted their recommendations./ag/ajx/nas

title: SES-IMAGOTAG :  Stifel confirms its recommendation on the share
full_text: Stifel confirms its Buy rating on SES-imagotag shares, with an unchanged target price of 190 euros. The analyst points out that the quotation of the world specialist in electronic labels was suspended yesterday after the publication of a Gotham City Research report attacking SES-imagotag on several points. Stifel states that it was not convinced by the arguments put forward, whether concerning the activity, the business model or the Walmart contract. Thus, 'we believe that SES-imagotag's strategy and business model remain totally relevant'. As for the Walmart contract, "even without the details, we have enough elements to consider it profitable", adds Stifel. The analyst admits only that he is not in a position to comment on the suspicions of accounting irregularities raised by Gotham City Research."We are not the group's auditors. Therefore, in the absence of any further information, we assume that the accounts certified by the auditors are accurate, and our recommendation and price target therefore remain unchanged', concludes the analyst. title: DANONE :  significant rerating potential according to Oddo BHF
full_text: Oddo BHF has reaffirmed its 'outperform' rating and 64-euro price target on Danone, believing that 'with a 2023 PE of less than 16 times, the potential for rerating remains significant as the company continues to refocus on its core business'.Pointing to a reassuring message from the food group on the second quarter, the research department is raising its forecasts to expect organic growth of +5.7% over this period, with +8.4% in prices and -2.6% in volume/mix.Oddo BHF is nevertheless revising its EPS forecasts for 2023 and 2024 (and beyond) downwards, due to more negative currency effects and an increase in its financial expenses forecast. title: Goldman starts Hellofresh with 'Neutral' - Target 22.90 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. investment bank Goldman Sachs has initiated its rating on the shares of Hellofresh with a "Neutral" rating at a target price of 22.90 euros. 2023 is a transitional year for European meal delivery companies, analyst Lisa Yang wrote in an industry report available Thursday. It is characterized by high Corona-era comparables, high inflation and weak consumer spending, she added. On the other hand, rationalization is helping profitability, she added. With the weak share price performance since the beginning of the year, she believes the uncertainties are priced in. However, the market now wants to see growth first and further industry consolidation. At Hellofresh, she praises the opportunities, but criticizes the high churn rates. Thus one needs further high marketing expenditures./ag/zb  Publication of the original study: 22.06.2023 / 01:09 / CEST First disclosure of original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / Time zone not specified in study

title: VIVENDI :  Oddo BHF reiterates its Outperform rating
full_text: Oddo BHF analysts question the possibility of Bolloré making a media acquisition alongside Vivendi. The group would use its cash to make a major acquisition, which could then serve as the basis for a merger with Vivendi. Compagnie de l'Odet could then retain control of the new merged entity," says Oddo BHF. The analyst reiterates his Outperform rating on Vivendi, with a target price of E13.' In view of the group's investment capacity (>E6bn), and assuming that the target is listed, this would lead to a valuation of around E4-5bn/$ maximum (and therefore ~E6bn with the premium). We could, for example, imagine the acquisition of Lions Gate ($2bn) or Simon & Schuster ($2bn) or both! says Oddo BHF.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: IDI  :  IDI forges ahead in 2023 with solid divestments
full_text:
IDI forges ahead in 2023 with solid divestmentsM&A /CORP. ACTION2023 is shaping up particularly well for IDI, which, after selling Freeland in March, is preparing to sell its stake in Flex Composite Group to Michelin for a total EV of €700m. The move should not only replenish IDI’s pockets, but it also demonstrates IDI’s ability to create value, with a return on investment of over 12x.FACT
IDI made its first investment in Flex Composite Group for €23.2m back in 2015. 
IDI and Andera Partners have announced an agreement to sell the entire Flex Composite Group to Michelin for an enterprise value of €700m. 
This amount corresponds to an investment multiple 12x higher than the initial investment. ANALYSISIDI kicked off 2023 on the right foot in terms of investments and divestments. Indeed, as of mid-2023, IDI had already completed four deals: the external growth of Talis Education into the Fore group and two disposals, including that of Freeland, the French leader in services to the self-employed, to MML Capital, enabling IDI to achieve a solid investment multiple of 2.2x and an IRR of c. 24% in less than four years. It is worth noting, however, that Freeland’s story is a little different, as IDI reinvested a significant part of the proceeds from the sale.
This morning, IDI announced that it is now the turn of Flex Composite Group to leave its portfolio. IDI and Andera Partners have signed an agreement to sell the entire Flex Composite Group (FCG) to Michelin for an enterprise value of €700m. This transaction would correspond to a substantial return on investment of 12x the initial outlay. As a reminder, FCG joined the IDI portfolio in 2015 for €23.2m. As of December 2022, IDI held 63.4% of the group alongside Andera Partners as minority investor.
Flex Composite Group is a European leader in the design, manufacture and distribution of advanced composite materials. The Group is now made up of three divisions: i) Engineered fabrics, the technical coated fabrics division, ii) Carbon fabrics and technical composites Composite Materials, and iii) a thermoplastic films division, Technical Films, all of which have enabled it to achieve sales of c.€200m in 2022. Starting in 2015 up to 2022, through IDI’s support of its development, FCG has generated an operating margin of between 25% and 30% and average organic growth of 11%.
The transaction is set to close in Q3 23, subject to approval by the competition authorities, and is further proof of IDI’s ability to create value.

title: GETLINK :  Morgan Stanley raises its recommendation
full_text: On Monday, Morgan Stanley raised its recommendation on Getlink to 'overweight' from 'in-line weighting', with a price target raised from 18.3 to 19 euros, believing that a favorable scenario was taking shape around the share.In a note published this morning, the intermediary points out that the Channel Tunnel operator has benefited from a constant factor in recent years, namely its solid price control.According to the intermediary, the Group could further strengthen its advantage thanks to the difficulties currently experienced by ferry companies, faced with both rising wages and future payments due to their CO2 emissions.In the medium term, these factors could boost Getlink's annual Ebitda to between €50 and €60 million, representing an addition of €1.5 to €2 to the share price, according to the analyst.Morgan Stanley also acknowledges having been too cautious regarding the recovery of the tourism and leisure sector, which has led it to revise its traffic forecasts upwards for 2023-2025, representing a bonus of €1.5 per share.Lastly, with regard to ElecLink - the high-voltage interconnection cable that runs under the Channel Tunnel - the professional points to payments likely to surprise on the upside in the medium term in view of current electricity market needs, a factor which he believes could add a further 1.1 euros per share.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SAINT-GOBAIN :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Saint-Gobain shares, with an unchanged target price of 70 euros. The analyst expects Q2 volumes to remain difficult, given the high basis for comparison (at least until the end of H1).  We are expecting Q2 sales of 11,978 ME, down 11%, and a negative perimeter effect of 4.5% (-1.9% L/L: prices +6.0%, volume -7.9%)", says Oddo BHF. For its part, the Visible Alpha consensus forecasts sales close to 12.4 billion euros.The broker remains convinced that Saint-Gobain still has the potential to surprise, particularly in H1. The consensus is for a 10% fall in annual EBIT, compared with a 5/10% rise for Sika and even >10% for Holcim. We are now expecting a decline of 6%, i.e. 4% above market expectations", says the broker. Oddo BHF believes that the changes of the last few years have not yet been fully integrated. title: Sartorius June gains evaporate after profit warning
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - With the lowering of Sartorius ' forecast, the recent rally in the laboratory equipment manufacturer's share price evaporated on Monday. At broker Lang & Schwarz, the Dax-listed shares lost a good twelve percent to 312 euros ahead of schedule. This means that the price gains achieved in June have been eroded.       This month, the shares had recovered by 15 percent to their high before the weekend, breaking the downward trend they had been on since February. Now, however, they are falling back sharply and in Xetra trading, at the current pre-Borussia discount, would be thrown back to the low for the year at the end of May.      Sartorius had issued a nasty sales and profit warning, a trader explained in the morning. Even if the warning is not completely unexpected, the share price is likely to come under heavy pressure.      Analyst Odysseas Manesiotis of Berenberg Bank had also feared a reduction in the annual targets, but it is now much stronger than expected. In discussions with management, it had become clear that there would be no improvement in the second quarter, and that the second half of the year would probably be the same as the first. According to Manesiotis, the market will only trust the medium-term confidence when the growth in orders is also reflected in the figures.       UBS criticized that in the conference call on the first quarter, management had still asserted that despite a weak performance, the full year would go according to plan. This assessment was obviously too optimistic./ajx/ag/men

title: JPMorgan sees high potential in Morphosys
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - U.S. bank JPMorgan is giving antibody specialist Morphosys plenty of advance praise months before the crucial data readout on its cancer drug pelabresib. More likely than failure is that the trial will be a success, industry expert James Gordon wrote in a report available Friday. But even with a 50/50 chance, the share, which is currently heading for 30 euros, still has an upside potential of around 40 percent. The expert therefore raised his rating by two notches from "Underweight" to "Overweight" and tripled the price target to 36 euros.      Morphosys had recently accelerated its work on pelabresib, the decisive data are now announced for the end of 2023. The drug is being tested in patients with myelofibrosis. Many experts refer to this rare disease as bone marrow cancer, but the experts at Morphosys see the causes in the blood. If the company achieves a breakthrough with the drug, many experts believe it has blockbuster potential - in other words, the chance to generate sales of at least a billion dollars a year.      Morphosys had brought pelabresib under its own roof in 2021 through the costly acquisition of the U.S. company Constellation Pharmaceuticals and has since put all its eggs in this basket. However, many experts, and now JPMorgan analyst Gordon, see a high chance that Morphosys can achieve its key goals of reducing spleen enlargement caused by the disease - as well as reducing symptoms. Such success would remove a lot of risk from the stock, the industry expert noted.      In the process, Gordon even credits the drug with a peak sales potential of $1.5 billion annually - which he believes would transform the small Morphosys company. After all, in 2022, for example, the Bavarians were still turning over just under 300 million euros. With the U.S. group Abbvie, according to the expert, a competitor in myelofibrosis could appear on the scene in the future, but according to the data to date, the drug of the Americans appears less tolerable and has a worse safety profile than Pelabresib.      JPMorgan had downgraded Morphosys shares to "underweight" from previously "neutral" at the start of the year. At the time, Gordon felt that the move was prompted primarily by the disappointing sales performance of Morphosysa's blood cancer drug Monjuvi, which also carried the risk of falling market expectations. However, this problem has now been amply overcome, the analyst judged.      According to the "Overweight" rating, JPMorgan expects the stock to outperform the respective sector in the next six to twelve months./tav/ag/jha/  Analyzing institute JPMorgan.   Publication of the original study: 15.06.2023 / 20:17 / BST First disclosure of the original study: 16.06.2023 / 00:15 / BST

title: SWISSQUOTE GROUP HOLDING  :  More rates, more money
full_text:
More rates, more moneyTARGET CHANGECHANGE IN TARGET PRICECHF 234 vs 213 +10.2%Our target price increase is mainly driven by our DCF update (see more details below). We have upgraded most of the financials, also positively impacting the Peer-based valuation. 
Overall, we confirm our very positive opinion on Swissquote, massively benefiting from the higher rates environment and believe in several catalysts ahead (M&A, innovation, some inflows from Credit Suisse notably). CHANGE IN EPS2023 : CHF 15.1 vs 13.5 +11.3%2024 : CHF 17.8 vs 15.9 +11.8%Our EPS forecast is massively increased as we have upgraded our net interest income expectations (from CHF144m and CHF184m for FY 23 and FY 24 to CHF198m and CHF233m for FY 23 and FY 24, respectively). This is mainly driven by continued interest rate hikes across Switzerland, the EU and the US. 
This incremental net interest income flows through the P&L with very few underlying costs. As a result, although we have slightly increased the cost base given Swissquote's tendency to leverage on highly profitable years to expand further, our pre-tax profit margin forecast increases from 48.5% and 49.9% for FY 23 and FY 24 to 49.7% and 51.1% for FY 23 and FY 24, respectively.CHANGE IN DCFCHF 250 vs 205 +22.1%As described in our EPS section, the DCF upgrade is driven by, overall a much stronger top line (from CHF486m and CHF557m for FY 23 and FY 24 to CHF541.5m and CHF618.8m for FY 22 and FY 24, respectively) while keeping a very stable cost base.

full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan has raised its rating on shares of Morphosys by two notches from "underweight" to "overweight". It also tripled its price target to 36 euros. "We are betting on pelabresib," analyst James Gordon wrote in a research note presented Friday. Phase III trial data are due at the end of the year for the bone marrow cancer drug. "It's more likely that the trial will be a success than that the drug will fail," the expert said. And even with a calculated 50/50 chance, there is immense upside potential with a target price of 36 euros, he added. Pelabresib is seen as a blockbuster candidate, which in the pharmaceutical sector are drugs with sales in the billions./ag/zb  Publication of the original study: 15.06.2023 / 20:17 / BST First disclosure of the original study: 16.06.2023 / 00:15 / BST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Carbios shares, with a price target raised from 45 to 64 euros, believing that the latest advances are reassuring and give cause for optimism.For the research firm, Carbios offers 'a disruptive enzymatic recycling solution for the plastic waste market'. title: S&P Global Ratings Downgrades Nasdaq Following Adenza Acquisition
full_text:
By Denny Jacob 
  S&P Global Ratings on Monday said it downgraded Nasdaq's long-term issuer credit ratings and senior unsecured notes to BBB from BBB+. 

  The ratings agency said the downgrade is a result of Nasdaq's planned acquisition of Adenza, which provides capital markets and regulatory solutions to financial institutions, for $10.5 billion and transaction costs, including $5.75 billion in cash and the remainder in common equity. 

  S&P said it expects the Adenza transaction to close within six to nine months and for Nasdaq to raise about $5.9 billion of new debt to fund the acquisition. The financing for the acquisition would weaken Nasdaq's financial risk profile, S&P said. 

  "Nasdaq's funds from operations to debt will drop well below 23% in the next two years, materially weaker than our previous base case, which did not consider the Adenza acquisition," S&P said. 
  Write to Denny Jacob at denny.jacob@wsj.com 
  (END) Dow Jones Newswires

  06-12-23 1045ET

title: Berenberg sees hardly any more price potential for Compugroup - downgrade
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX) - The private bank Berenberg sees hardly any more price drivers for the Compugroup share in the short term. Therefore, analyst Wolfgang Specht downgraded the paper of the software provider specialized in medical practices and hospitals from "Buy" to "Hold". The price target was left at 56 euros. In view of the price loss on this day, which according to traders is mainly a reaction to the Berenberg study, this currently means, however, again a potential of about 22 percent for the share.      Specht pointed out that Compugroup shares had far outperformed both the TecDax and the shares of competitor Nexus in the year to date.      The expert believes the company's annual targets are achievable and left his estimates for 2023 and 2024 unchanged. However, Specht believes it will be difficult to achieve profitability (adjusted Ebitda margin) of 27 percent by 2025 due to the necessary investments and the continued need for qualified personnel.      With a "Hold" recommendation, Berenberg sees limited upside or downside potential without an immediate share price driver./edh/ck/jha/  Analyzing institute Berenberg. title: Nexans soars, boosted by BofA recommendation upgrade
full_text: The share price of Nexans, the producer of fiber optic and copper cables, jumped on the stock market Monday morning, supported by a recommendation upgrade from Bank of America (BofA).               The share price was up 8.44% at 09:01 GMT to 79.05 euros on the Paris Bourse, the best performance of the CAC40, which was up 0.83% at the same time.               The stock was supported by Bank of America's change of recommendation to "buy" from "underperform", with a target price of 100 euros.               The company's exposure to renewable energies, its presence in the United States and its discount to the sector, which has reached 40% since the beginning of the year, justify the change of recommendation, explains BofA in a note. (Reported by Corentin Chappron, edited by Kate Entringer)

title: SHARES FLASH :  Volkswagen in demand - 'HB' with details on restructuring.
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - A report in "Handelsblatt" with details of a major restructuring is going down well with Volkswagen investors on Monday. The plans had already been reported by "Manager Magazin," but there were now more details about the cost-cutting plans, said Stifel expert Daniel Schwarz. On Xetra, the plus was recently about two percent. With up to 129.26 euros, the price rose to a high since March.      According to the "Handelsblatt", the group's CEO Oliver Blume is planning the "biggest restructuring in decades". The business newspaper refers to an unnamed top manager. CEO Oliver Blume will present the plan to the Supervisory Board on Tuesday, it said. In the brand group for the mass market, earnings are to be increased by around three billion euros annually, thanks among other things to efficient development work and higher capacity utilization.      In the article, analyst Schwarz highlighted profitability targets for individual divisions that were significantly above expectations. He said this applied to the Audi margin range, which at 12 to 14 percent was higher than the previous range of 9 to 11 percent. For the core VW brand, 6.5 percent is planned instead of the more than 6 percent previously mentioned, he added./tih/mis

title: ABIVAX :  Portzamparc downgrades its recommendation
full_text: On Friday, Portzamparc downgraded its recommendation on Abivax shares from 'buy' to 'hold', following the stock's 'exceptional' performance since the start of the year.The research firm, which explains that it is waiting for more attractive entry points, says it remains optimistic about the biotech company's future developments.Referring to a possible "success story" in the making, the analyst stresses that the excellent clinical results unveiled recently are leading him to be more aggressive in his assumptions.He thus raises the potential market share of obefazimod, the company's main drug candidate, in ulcerative colitis (UC) from 12.5% to 15%, which leads him to raise his target price on the stock from 15.5 to 17 euros.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ROTHSCHILD & CO :  Oddo BHF remains 'neutral' and adjusts its target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'neutral' rating on Rothschild & Co. shares, with a price target reduced from 48 to 46.6 euros, 'in order to take into account the payment of the 2022 ordinary dividend of 1.4 E paid last week', explains the analyst.Oddo BHF also refers to the project of Concordia (holding company of the Rothschild family), which yesterday filed a simplified tender offer for Rothschild & Co shares at a price of 46.6 E per share, with the intention of requesting the implementation of a squeeze-out.  As a reminder, the price of E46.6 will be adjusted to E38.6 following the detachment of the exceptional distribution of E8 per share", the broker points out. title: Barclays lowers target for Wacker Chemie to 193 euros - 'Overweight'
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX) - British investment bank Barclays cut its price target for Wacker Chemie to 193 euros from 202 euros, but kept its rating at "overweight." The shares are caught between cyclical headwinds and structural potential, analyst Sebastian Satz wrote in a research note issued Friday. Wacker is currently one of the most short sold stocks in the European chemicals sector, the expert said. He cut his operating earnings (Ebitda) estimate for 2023 and is now 15 percent below consensus. However, despite all the risks to annual targets, he considers the overall risk/reward ratio to be attractive./ag/mis      Publication of the original study: 08.06.2023 / 20:22 / GMT  First disclosure of the original study: 09.06.2023 / 04:10 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: SOITEC :  Stifel reiterates its Buy recommendation
full_text: Stifel remains Buy on Soitec shares, with a price target of 170E.The analyst is reassured by Soitec's confirmed targets for fiscal 2026, namely sales of 2.1 billion dollars and an EBITDA margin of 40%.' This target should be achieved thanks to the structural growth of the semiconductor market in general, the growing adoption of innovative substrates and the expansion of Soitec's product portfolio with new products such as the SmartSiC solution ', the broker continues.Although the most recent data suggest persistent weakness in smartphone demand ' and a prolonged period of inventory absorption in the supply chain in the short term ', Stifel believes that investors are well aware of this risk, and reiterates its buy recommendation.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JPMorgan puts FMC on 'Negative Catalyst Watch'
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - Analyst David Adlington of U.S. bank JPMorgan is skeptical for FMC ahead of upcoming, current proposals for reimbursements for dialysis treatments (ESRD) in the U.S. health insurance system at the end of June or beginning of July. Accordingly, it gave the dialysis group's shares "Negative Catalyst Watch" status. The fundamental rating also remains "Underweight." Adlington raised his price target from 17.40 to 28.60 euros, but it remains well below the current Xetra price. In view of hefty cost increases in 2022, investors probably expected above-average reimbursements for the coming year, the expert said. However, current signals point to the opposite./ag/mis      Publication of the original study: 08.06.2023 / 19:43 / BST  First disclosure of the original study: 09.06.2023 / 00:15 / BST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Jefferies leaves Delivery Hero at 'Buy' - 'Sleeping Giant'
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - Analysts Jefferies left its rating on shares of Delivery Hero at "buy" with a price target of 87 euros. A "sleeping giant" is the food delivery company, analyst Giles Thorne wrote in a study presented on Friday. However, also with a gigantically inflated balance sheet. Thorne even considers it the weakest in the industry. On the other hand, however, it has the greatest operating earnings potential. In Thorne's view, it is now clear that investors in 2023 are demanding growth, cash flow and healthy balance sheets. Accordingly, Delivery Hero is currently his last choice in the sector. However, he still sees value and valuation room./ag/mis      Original study publication date: 08.06.2023 / 14:58 / ET  First disclosure of the original study: 08.06.2023 / 19:00 / ET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Atos: share price up, an analyst's opinion
full_text: Atos gains nearly 2% in Paris as Invest Securities confirms its buy rating on the stock this morning, with an unchanged target price of 18 euros, after yesterday's Tech Foundations CMD confirmed the positive progress made since the 2nd half of '22.If this division succeeds in achieving its 2026 objectives, it is clear in our minds that its valuation will be significantly higher than the one retained today", the analyst assesses.According to Invest, this execution could nevertheless be called into question if rumors of the sale of Tech Foundations to D. Kretinsky on the basis of an aberrant valuation were to be confirmed."Between now and the AGM on June 28, uncertainty will prevail, with the slingshot led by Sycomore as another factor of uncertainty. For this reason, we will wait before integrating Tech Foundations' new ambitions, as well as the favorable outcome of the Trizetto litigation", concludes the broker.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: VERALLIA :  BofA resumes coverage with a buy recommendation
full_text: Bank of America announced on Thursday that it had resumed coverage of Verallia shares, with a Buy recommendation and a price target of 43 euros.In a research note, the American bank stresses that the European leader in glass packaging is benefiting from buoyant winds over the long term with the end of plastic products, a market estimated at $300 billion.According to the firm, demand for glass packaging should thus grow by 2% to 3% per year in Europe.BofA, which highlights Verallia's 'darling' status in terms of ESG issues, says it expects Ebitda to be 6% to 8% above consensus for fiscal 2023 and 2024.The bank adds that Verallia's share price is based on an Enterprise Value/Ebitda ratio of around 4.7x by 2024, showing a discount to its peers (6.5-7x) despite higher margins.BofA says it has added the stock to its list of best investment ideas for small and mid-caps.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: Berenberg on Thursday renewed its 'sell' recommendation and 100 euro price target on Airbus, judging that it was 'too early to extrapolate' the good delivery figures published for May.The aircraft manufacturer announced last night that it had delivered 63 aircraft and booked 17 gross orders last month, compared with 54 aircraft delivered and only four gross orders in April.According to Berenberg, the aerospace giant still has its work cut out for it in the second half of the year, as it has so far delivered only 244 aircraft out of its target of 720 deliveries, corresponding to a ratio of 34%, compared with an average of 38% for this period of the year.While we like the company and its investment case on a number of points, we find it hard to envisage any expansion in valuation multiples from their current levels, and still believe that the earnings consensus is 10% to 15% too high for the next 12 to 24 months", he concludes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ATOS :  Oddo BHF raises its target price on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'underperform' rating on Atos, with a price target raised from 10.6 to 12.7 euros. The analyst points out that Atos held an analysts' meeting yesterday dedicated to Tech Foundations (TFCo), the aim of which was to present an update on 2026 ambitions.In this context, Atos reiterated "with confidence" FY 2023 guidance at group level (org growth of 1% and +1%; op. margin of 4% and 5%.), as well as specific soft guidance for TFCo (activity decline of c. -5% org and positive op. margin). In terms of sales, Atos now expects TFCo sales to bottom out at 5 billion euros by 2024 (vs. the previous low point of 4.1 billion euros in 2024). This new guidance implies a decline of -5% for 2023 and 2024 (vs. c. -10% prev.)Oddo BHF reports that Atos' Board of Directors still seems to be negotiating a possible sale of TFCo, potentially for a negative value, and is looking to sell a significant stake in Eviden, which suggests that the situation is less favorable than exposed yesterday. The analyst therefore confirms his negative opinion on the stock.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Hugo Boss 'back in fashion' - UBS starts with a 'buy' rating
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX) - The turnaround at fashion manufacturer Hugo Boss has only just begun in the view of major Swiss bank UBS. The fashion manufacturer's margin potential is still underestimated, it said, adding that the stock is undervalued compared to its peers. "Hugo Boss is back in fashion," Susy Tibaldi wrote in a research note available Wednesday. The analyst attributes this in part to an effective social media campaign over the past year and a half that has made Hugo Boss more relevant among its young target audience.      On the popular platform TikTok alone, the fashion manufacturer has gained more followers than its three subsequent competitors combined. Tibaldi also praises the focus on more casual wear as well as women's fashion, which has given Hugo Boss more reach. This, he said, was also accompanied by a remodeling of stores. As a result, sales picked up more than expected - and that was in only the second year of the brand's relaunch.      UBS therefore includes Hugo Boss in its valuation with "Buy" and issues a price target of 87 euros. With this target, Tibaldi trusts the MDax-listed stock to return to the level of 2015. At that time, the stock had reached its record high of 120.40 euros, before collapsing to one-sixth of that value by March 2020. On Wednesday morning, the share rose strongly in the direction of 68 euros.      Compared to its peers, Hugo Boss shares are undervalued, Tibaldi wrote. Despite above-average growth in earnings per share, the discount to the rest of the industry is around 20 percent.       The fashion manufacturer's margin potential, in particular, is underestimated and could open up a whole new chapter. This is because freight costs have now normalized, while Hugo Boss has raised the prices of its own products. According to Tibaldi, this should more than compensate for the ongoing investments in brand and digitization in the future.      Tibaldi is also betting on the upcoming Capital Markets Day on June 15, which could become a potential price driver for Hugo Boss shares. The fashion manufacturer could raise its targets beyond current expectations. In doing so, the UBS analyst has faith in the group's brand momentum, even in the face of macroeconomic headwinds and tepid consumer sentiment, which, however, poses a risk to her optimistic forecast.      With a "buy" rating, UBS expects the stock's total return (share price gain plus dividend) to exceed the market's expected return by at least six percent over the next twelve months./niw/ag/mis      Analyzing institute UBS. title: Berenberg raises target for SNP to 33.50 euros - 'Hold'
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX) - Private bank Berenberg has raised its price target for SNP from 25.00 to 33.50 euros, but left its rating at "Hold". With the new target, analyst Wolfgang Specht took into account the high of Octapharma's voluntary takeover bid for SNP in a study presented on Tuesday. Its main reason is likely to be the personal interests of Octapharma owner and SNP major shareholder Wolfgang Marguerre. The dispute between Marguerre and the SNP board is likely to continue. With a qualified majority in SNP, Marguerre could make far-reaching decisions, although his interest in a majority of more than two-thirds could be limited, Specht believes. The operating environment is likely to remain mixed, and valuations are not cheap, he says. In the short term, however, the shares should trade close to the offer./gl/ck      Publication of the original study: 05.06.2023 / 16:35 / GMT  First disclosure of original study: Date not stated in study / Time not stated in study / Time zone not stated in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Citi lowers Pfandbriefbank to 'Sell' - Concerns in commercial real estate
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX) - According to US bank Citigroup, Deutsche Pfandbriefbank could not avoid higher provisions. The market for commercial real estate is in a downturn, investor demand is weakening and prices are falling, wrote analyst Borja Ramirez Segura according to a study available on Tuesday.      As a result, he is now more cautious than the average analyst on the real estate financier's loan loss provisions item. He downgraded the shares listed in the SDax, the index of smaller stocks, from "neutral" to "sell." He cut the price target from 8.60 to 6.10 euros, which means he sees further downside potential of more than ten percent.      In his base scenario, Ramirez Segura expects commercial property prices to fall by an average of 20 to 30 percent in the current and coming year. In a vulnerability analysis he has prepared, this would mean additional loan loss provisions of around EUR 100 million, which he expects to be split in half between 2023 and 2024.      He therefore lowered his estimates for the specialty bank's earnings per share. His forecasts are now ten percent below the market estimate. Looking at the hard core capital ratio, which stood at 16.6 percent at the end of the first quarter, the bank is in a "solid position" despite everything, he said.      With a "sell" rating, Citigroup predicts a negative total return for the stock over the next twelve months./ajx/ck/jha/  Analyzing institute Citigroup.      Publication of the original study: 06.06.2023 / 00:00 / ET      First disclosure of original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / Time zone not specified in study

title: SPIE :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Spie shares, with an unchanged target price of 32 euros. The analyst points out that "the fundamentals (sales and margins) are still in good shape for Q2", following on from the excellent performance of Q1. In Q1, for example, the Group recorded very strong organic growth of 10.9%. For Q2 2023, the basis of comparison remains favorable (Q2 2022 +4.9% LFL) and the Group continues to state that it is not seeing any slowdown in its various markets", says Oddo BHF, adding that "the order book remains very solid". Spie confirmed that it would remain very active to seize opportunities in the coming months. The Group has considerable room for maneuver, with FCF that we believe will remain > 300 ME", stresses Oddo BHF. The broker is targeting organic growth of around 6% for the full year. We remain convinced of the Group's strengths: 1/ dynamic activity; 2/ ability to improve margins despite the inflationary context; 3/ sound balance sheet', concludes Oddo BHF. title: TRANSGENE :  Invest Securities confirms its Buy rating
full_text: Invest Securities confirms its Buy rating on Transgene shares, with an unchanged target price of 5.4 euros.  Benefiting from extensive media coverage since the weekend, Transgene's share price jumped +22% yesterday (and +40% at its peak) following the presentation of updated data on its personalized head and neck cancer vaccine at the ASCO congress", stresses the analyst.The results seem "very promising" in terms of the vaccine's therapeutic potential.  Biologically, the results remain consistent with the demonstration of a strong specific immune response induced by the vaccine, and a correlation with the observed clinical benefit", concludes the broker. title: Deutsche Pfandbriefbank lose after Citi sell recommendation
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - The shares of Deutsche Pfandbriefbank reacted to a sell recommendation by Citigroup with clear losses on Tuesday. On the trading platform Tradegate, they fell compared to the Xetra closing price of the previous day last by 2.1 percent to 7.15 euros.       Citigroup analyst Borja Ramirez Segura downgraded the papers of the real estate financier from "Neutral" to "Sell" and lowered the price target from 8.60 to 6.10 euros. He justified this by pointing out that the commercial real estate markets are in a downturn with falling prices and declining investor demand. The expert is therefore more cautious than the average analyst about the bank's loan loss provisions./edh/mis

title: TRANSGENE :  Invest Securities reiterates its recommendation
full_text: Transgene presented updated results from its Ph II study in HPV-16 positive anogenital cancers at ASCO 2023. Following this presentation, Invest Securities confirms its Buy recommendation on the stock and its price target of 5.4 E.'The data highlight a strong correlation between observed immunological responses and clinical responses. Indeed, the strongest clinical responses were obtained in patients who also showed the strongest immune responses against HPV antigens E6 and E7', says the analyst.  At this stage, 58% of patients who received the TG4001/avelumab combo showed an increase in immune responses against HPV, compared with 9% of patients who received avelumab alone. In addition, 11 of the 13 patients who developed an immune response showed stabilization or even regression, underlining the correlation between biological and clinical responses' adds Invest Securities.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Deutsche Bank Research leaves Verbio at 'Buy' - Target 50 euros

title: Cleaner targets - JPMorgan upgrades Heidelberg Materials
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - The European building materials industry is getting cleaner, according to US bank JPMorgan. The companies' decarbonization targets led to the industry's fundamentals improving, subsequently resulting in stronger pricing power. JPMorgan analyst Elodie Rall wrote this in an industry report released Thursday, upgrading Heidelberg Materials to "overweight" from "neutral" - with a price target raised to 80 euros from 66 euros.      According to Rall, Heidelberg Materials has the most ambitious decarbonization targets in the industry. As a result, the group will ultimately be able to produce cleaner cement products and will then be able to demand almost three times the current cement price in the trade.      In the short term, there are question marks regarding sustainable pricing and declining volumes until 2024, so Rall refrains from issuing an "overweight" recommendation for the sector as a whole. However, she sees the greatest opportunities for Heidelberger.      The expert raised her operating earnings estimates for the DAX-listed group for this year. Her forecast for earnings before interest and taxes (EBIT) is now ten percent above the upper end of the target range formulated by the company.      The Heidelberg Materials share is also attractive from a valuation point of view. The stock is currently trading at a 25 percent discount to its long-term average compared with the European cement sector, which is trading at a 17 percent discount.      According to its "Overweight" rating, JPMorgan expects the share to outperform the respective sector over the next six to twelve months./ajx/tih/jha/  Analyzing institute JPMorgan. title: NACON :  Oddo BHF slightly reduces its target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Nacon shares, with a slightly reduced target price, from 3.7 to 3.5 euros. Last night, Nacon published results in line with expectations, with full-year sales already reported at 156 ME (stable compared with the previous year), gross margin up 18% to 92.1 ME and net income (NI) up 28% to 12.8 ME (vs. 10.9 MEe). As for the outlook for 2023/24, Nacon is not disclosing any guidance at this stage, but confirms its line-up of some twenty games, compared with 13 a year earlier.Nacon is, however, sidestepping the failure of the Gollum release (last May 25). According to the analyst, the 'bad buzz' surrounding this game, developed by Deadelic, is clearly detrimental to sales in the short term, with an impact of around 5% on EPS, but it 'does not call into question the prospect of a marked rebound in results this year', After a financial year 2022/23 far from the Group's initial objectives, the bad buzz about Gollum is not likely to reassure in a context that remains delicate in the sector, and the share's reaction over one week attests to this (-21%)", analyzes Oddo BHF.  However, despite the failure of Gollum, which we are taking into account in our new forecasts, the line-up looks set to be fairly dynamic over the next few months, with content that seems to us to be of much higher quality", concludes the broker. title: MERCIALYS  :  AlphaValue lowers its price target
full_text: On Tuesday, AlphaValue lowered its price target for Mercialys from 11.8 to 11.2 euros, while renewing its buy recommendation on the share.In a note published in the afternoon, the research firm explains that it fears that rising financial expenses will eventually penalize the retail real estate group's earnings from operations (FFO) by 2026.However, the Paris-based consultancy notes that the company's net financial debt (LTV) ratio, which stood at 34% at the end of 2022, seems much more manageable than that of some of its competitors.AlphaValue considers this factor to be at the heart of its investment theory for the stock, which it is not yet ready to give a speculative premium to, given its free float, which is flirting with 100%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: Allowing for the 2022 actual figures and MAC restructuring effortsEPS CHANGECHANGE IN EPS2023 : € 0.30 vs 0.37 -19.2%2024 : € 0.33 vs 0.38 -13.5%We have trimmed our 2023 forecasts somewhat to allow for continuing restructuring efforts at the MAC business unit that are due to last into 2024. title: Coface: Berenberg raises its target, the share price advances
full_text: Coface is one of the biggest risers on the SBF 120 index on Tuesday morning on the Paris Bourse, following a target upgrade by Berenberg, which considers the credit insurance specialist to be "in a class of its own".At around 10:00 a.m., the French group's shares gained around 1.2%, while the SBF 120 lost around 0.4% at the time.Berenberg announced this morning that it had raised its target from 16.8 to 17.2 euros, while renewing its buy recommendation.We believe that Coface is now the best of the big three credit insurers, which is why the stock deserves to be traded at a premium in terms of valuation", explains the German bank.According to Berenberg, the company stands out on a whole series of performance indicators compared with its rivals Atradius and Allianz Trade, particularly with regard to the combined ratio.This leads us to believe that Coface is in a class of its own", he concludes in a note.On the stock market, Coface shares soared by more than 10% on Friday, following the release of first-quarter results showing a very good start to the year. The stock has gained over 11% since January 1.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: NEXITY  :  AlphaValue upgrades to 'sell'.
full_text: AlphaValue announced on Monday that it had upgraded its rating on Nexity shares to 'sell' from 'reduce', and lowered its target price to 16.5 euros from 23.2 euros.In a research note, the analyst explains that, in his opinion, investors tend to underestimate the adjustment that the French property development sector is currently undergoing, a movement similar to that experienced by other European countries, at a time when there are no signs of a turnaround in interest rates before the second half of 23.To be clear, we are very concerned about the 2024-25 horizon and are further reducing our EPS forecasts", he adds, judging that the 8% operating margin achieved last year will not be repeated this year.According to AlphaValue, Nexity will have to arbitrate between its volume of activity and its level of operating profitability in order to keep its results afloat.The intermediary also considers that the dividend of 2.50 euros per share paid in respect of the 2023 financial year does not seem any more sustainable.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CHARGEURS  :  Adjustments to our FY 23-24 estimates
full_text: Adjustments to our FY 23-24 estimates EPS CHANGECHANGE IN EPS2023 : € 0.80 vs 1.24 -35.2%2024 : € 1.20 vs 1.66 -27.8%We have revised our FY 23-24 assumptions following the Q1-23 release. We now estimate sales for 2023 at €788m versus €831m previously, and the underlying operating profit at 6.1% versus 7.2%. This decline is due to a downward revision in the sales and margins at Chargeurs Advanced Materials, on which we had been overly optimistic after an exceptionally high level in Q1-22 due to a post-Covid catch-up effect. We had also been too optimistic on Chargeurs Luxury Materials, with a sales growth forecast of 7%, despite the particularly high level of activity in 2022. We have also reduced our estimates for the HealthCare Solution division (with sales growth of 0% vs. 30% previously), as we no longer have any visibility on the division's revenues and margins in the context of an improving healthcare situation. For 2025, however, we are more optimistic, estimating strong sales growth for Chargeurs Museum Studio (+25%) to over €200m with a margin of 12%, 10% for Chargeurs Luxury Materials to €110m with a margin of c.4% and 50% for Chargeurs Personal Goods to c.€24m with a margin of 10%.CHANGE IN NAV€ 41.1 vs 38.0 +7.98%Our NAV has increased on the back of updated EV/EBITDA multiples and peer groups. We now use average estimated EBITDA for 23/24 and 25. As a result, Chargeurs Advanced Materials has seen its value drop significantly, with a multiple of 11.5x versus 14.5x previously, while Chargeurs Fashion Technologies' value has risen sharply due to a change in methodology, from an EV/EBITDA of 9x to an EV/EBITDA of 11.6x. Finally, we have applied an EV/EBITDA of 11.4x for Chargeurs Museum Studio, compared with 10.5x previously.CHANGE IN DCF€ 26.2 vs 28.7 -8.57%Our DCF-based valuation is reduced slightly from €28.76 to €26.20 after incorporating our adjustment to the FY23-24 EPS forecast (see EPS commentary). We expect revenues of around €788m (vs. €831m) for FY 2023 with an underlying profit of c.€34m (vs.€51m) and €872m (vs. €892m) for FY2024 with an underlying operating profit of €53m (vs. €67m). We are also less optimistic on the WCR, which we had underestimated due to the extremely low level in 2021 (3.8% of sales).

full_text: Invest Securities has adjusted its recommendation on Foncière Lyonnaise (SFL) shares from "buy" to "sell", with a significantly reduced target price from 91.8 to 60.6 euros. title: CHARGEURS  :  Heading for a Chargeurs Advanced Materials rebound?
full_text:
Heading for a Chargeurs Advanced Materials rebound? EARNINGS/SALES RELEASESDespite Chargeurs’ somewhat expected 18% lfl yoy revenue contraction in Q1 ‘23 due to the record 2022 Q1, Chargeurs Advanced Materials showed signs of a volume recovery with 21% qoq volume growth. This business line is responding to the wait-and-see attitude in particular in China by expanding geographically and premiumizing. The Q1-23 confirmed the Group’s new growth drivers, with Chargeurs PCC Fashion Technologies’ business holding at high levels and Chargeurs Museum Studio posting a solid 30.2% lfl yoy growth. Following these results, Chargeurs confirmed its scenario of positive trends in the H2 23.FACT
Chargeurs reported total revenue of €169.7m in Q1-23, down 16.6% yoy (18% organically). Over the quarter, revenues were down slightly by 2% but grew organically by 0.6%.
The decline in sales compared with Q1-22 was attributable to Chargeurs Advanced Materials (-27% organic growth yoy to €70.7m) due to an unfavorable basis of comparison with a post-Covid catch-up effect. CAM’s revenues, however, highlighted an inflection point with a positive volume effect of 21% over the quarter and revenue growth of 8.6% on a quarterly basis. 
Although down by 6% yoy, the Fashion Technologies business line maintained high levels at €51.3m (-0.2% organically). 
In the Luxury division, Chargeurs Museum Studio activity continued to expand, with organic growth of 30.2% yoy to €24m. 
Lastly, Chargeurs Luxury Fibers was down 30% yoy on an organic basis to €21.7m but up 17.3% qoq.Revenue break-down by divisionANALYSISChargeurs posted a revenue down 16.6% yoy or 18% organically to €169.7m.  The Group’s business was weighed down by Advanced Materials and Luxury Fibers , which had a record base of comparison. On a quarterly basis, however, Chargeurs posted organic growth of 0.6%, boosted by these same businesses. 
An inflection point for Advanced Materials?
Despite a 27% organic decline in sales yoy to €70.7m, Chargeurs Advanced Materials (CAM) recorded qoq growth of 8.6%. The Q1-22 comparison was unfavorable, as it had benefited from the strong demand driven by post-Covid inventory rebuilding. While volumes have naturally declined over the last three quarters on the back of inventory normalization and customer de-stocking, the 21% volume increase experienced in Q1-23 suggests that this process has now bottomed out. Although the prospects for a recovery in China have yet to be confirmed, the division has been able to recover by diversifying geographically, notably in India and Australia, and by extending its offering to the premium segment. Based on these results, Chargeurs confirmed its forecast for a rebound in CAM’s business in H2-23. 
Chargeurs PCC Fashion Technologies holds its own in today’s challenging environment
Chargeurs PCC Fashion Technologies held its own in Q1 23 with a slight organic decline of 0.2% yoy to €51.3m. This performance was underpinned by the business line’s pricing power and a volume effect resulting from diversification, along with market share gains, despite a lagging recovery in Asia. Europe and South America continue to lead the way, and the Group remains optimistic barring a collapse in global consumption. 
Chargeurs Museum Studio affirms its status as the new growth driver
Chargeurs Museum Studio confirmed its momentum with a 30.2% organic increase in revenue to €24m. Going forward, the division is maintaining its target of €120m in revenues by 2023. Chargeurs reaffirmed its outlook for higher margins in H2 23/24 and 24/25 due to the phasing of large projects won in 2021 and 2022. The growth outlook remains good for the business line, which is currently in discussions in India and Central Asia to round out its exposure in Europe and North America.
Solid quarterly momentum for Chargeurs Luxury Fibers
Despite a 30% organic decline in revenue to €21.7m, Chargeurs Luxury Fibers (CLF) got the year off to a good start with growth of 17.3% qoq and the healthy dynamic for its premium wool label, NATIVA. Looking ahead, CLF aims to position itself as the market leader in eco-fibers (currently wool and, in the coming months, cashmere and cotton) and intends to expand its partnerships, as it did with Gucci at the end of 2022.
Outlook for the coming years
While no new information was provided, Chargeurs confirmed its ambition to make a major acquisition in the Luxury division in 2023 to rebalance the revenue contributions of its Technologies and Luxury businesses. Chargeurs reiterated its outlook for a strong 2023 and revenues of more than €1bn with EBIT of €100m excluding acquisitions by 2025.IMPACTOur model is currently being revised to incorporate these results. We will adjust downward our revenue and margin estimates for FY23-24 because we were overly optimistic. We are, however, maintaining our positive stance on the stock.

full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. investment bank Goldman Sachs lowered its price target for Rheinmetall from 305 to 304 euros, but left its rating at "buy." title: UBS raises target for Covestro to 41 euros - 'Neutral'
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Swiss major bank UBS raised its price target for Covestro to 41 euros from 39 euros after an investor conference and left its rating at "Neutral". One of the key conclusions of the event was that there was no discernible improvement from the first quarter to the second quarter in the end markets of consumer goods and industrial chemicals companies, with the notable exception of Covestro, analyst Andrew Stott wrote in an industry report available Monday. However, with destocking nearly complete, the outlook for the second half of 2023 has improved, he said. Pressure on manufacturing costs is less acute, thanks largely to lower energy prices, he added./edh/tih  Original study publication date: 05/19/2023 / 16:37 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 19.05.2023 / 16:37 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Bernstein leaves BMW at 'Market-Perform' - Target 110 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. analyst firm Bernstein Research left its rating on BMW at "Market-Perform" with a price target of 110 euros. The conditions for this year were not good at all in the auto sector, but after five months a positive conclusion can be drawn, analyst Daniel Roeska wrote in a study presented on Monday. The feared widespread deterioration of the market situation has failed to materialize; rather, the opposite is the case with a recovery in the USA, for example. In China, a recovery is also taking shape, and in Europe, thick order books and falling costs are helping./tih/ajx  Publication of the original study: 22.05.2023 / 04:34 / UTC First disclosure of the original study: 22.05.2023 / 04:34 / UTC----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Deutsche Bank Research downgrades Telefonica Deutschland to 'Hold'.
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Deutsche Bank Research downgraded Telefonica Deutschland to "hold" from "buy" and lowered its price target to 3.10 euros from 3.50 euros. Analyst Keval Khiroya referred to his earlier scenario in a report available Friday, saying Telefonica Deutschland should benefit from solid earnings in mobile wholesale, while the rollout of a mobile network at 1&1 could create uncertainty. As a result, Telefonica Deutschland's shares would have outperformed 1&1's by 50 percent in six months. However, because 1&1 now appears better positioned in terms of longer-term free cash, he now recommends a buy on 1&1 and only a hold on Telefonica Deutschland/bek/ajx  Publication of the original study: 19.05.2023 / Time not specified in study / CEST First disclosure of the original study: 19.05.2023 / 06:45 / CEST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: ELIOR GROUP :  UBS confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: UBS considers Elior Group's Q1 2023 results to be broadly in line. title: VALLOUREC :  Oddo remains Buy, target set at E21
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its EBITDA guidance unchanged (the analyst was already 5%> pre-release consensus expectations) as well as its Outperform opinion with a price target of 21 E.  The Group's EBITDA came out at 320 ME (vs. 312 ME in Q4 2022 and 45 ME in Q1 2022), benefiting in particular from its commercial strategy (focused on high value-added products), efforts on administrative, commercial and research costs (5.9% of sales vs. 9.3% a year ago), and of course a very favorable pricing environment in North America', says the analyst's office.  Adjusted FCF is 194 ME (-210 ME in Q1 22) and after taking into account mainly restructuring costs (47 ME), FCF reaches 151 ME. All in all, the Group reduced its debt by 130 ME, with net debt coming out at 1 BnE' stresses Oddo BHF. The analyst points out that the Group has confirmed its 2023 guidance, i.e. EBITDA growth, positive FCF (excluding asset disposals) and debt reduction. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Jefferies leaves Brenntag at 'Hold' - Target 76 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - Analysts Jefferies left Brenntag at "Hold" with a price target of 76 euros. Following the chemicals trader's first-quarter figures, analyst Chris Counihan raised his operating profit (Ebitda) estimates only slightly, still just below the lower end of the company's forecast. Sustained development in the Essentials business appears challenging, while the extent of weakness in the Specialties business was the biggest surprise of the quarterly report, he wrote in a research note available Thursday. Brenntag's performance in this area was weaker than all of its competitors. This suggests that earnings development is increasingly fraught with uncertainty, with an uncertain economic outlook./ajx/mis      Publication of the original study: 17.05.2023 / 13:03 / ET First disclosure of the original study: 17.05.2023 / 19:01 / ET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: TRIGANO :  Oddo BHF raises its price target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Trigano shares, with its target price raised from €148 to €160. The analyst's opinion is based in particular on Trigano's half-year results, which were 'slightly ahead of expectations', with ROC of 173.4 ME (compared with 169.2 ME anticipated). Given the high level of the order book, which is saturating production capacity, Trigano expects sales to progress well, and is "very confident" that motorhome sales will continue to grow beyond 2023.Oddo BHF therefore raises its OIR assumptions by 7% to 400 ME for the second half of the year. full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Shares in former SDax company SNP Schneider-Neureither & Partner made strong gains on Wednesday following a takeover bid from pharmaceuticals manufacturer Octapharma. They last gained 9.3 percent to 34.00 euros, which now puts them above Octapharma's bid. The Swiss want to pay 33.50 euros in cash per share in the Heidelberg-based software and consulting company. title: SAP lurk after higher targets on chart breakout
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - In the barely moving Dax, papers of SAP gained on Wednesday in view of higher medium-term targets. Shares in the Walldorf-based company gained 1.9 percent to 123.66 euros.       They thus lurked on a continuation of this year's upward trend, which had taken them to their highest level since early 2022 at 124.60 euros at the end of April, with a total gain of just over 29 percent.      SAP raised its 2025 outlook for nearly all key metrics for continuing operations. The company also announced a billion-euro share buyback.       Analyst Mohammed Moawalla of Goldman Sachs, speaking at the company's ongoing Sapphire customer show, said he was pleased not only with the targets and shareholder participation, but also the reaffirmed investment in development./ag/zb
