title: Ose Immuno: share price falls, broker lowers target
full_text: Ose Immunotherapeutics is down just under 1% in Paris, as Invest Securities this morning confirmed its buy rating on the stock, with a price target lowered from 10.3 to 8.26 euros. The analyst reports that on Friday after trading, OSE Immuno announced that it had regained the rights to OSE-127 after Servier decided not to pursue development of this asset following the failure of Phase IIa in Sjögren's syndrome.' As a reminder, in 2016, the two groups had entered into a collaboration to address autoimmune diseases with OSE-127 as part of 2 clinical trials conducted in parallel. Servier had placed a license option on OSE-127, which it therefore decided not to exercise, thereby cancelling out the potential for an associated milestone of 15mE ', the analyst points out. Invest Securities has thus adjusted its model by withdrawing the Sjögren's syndrome program line, but remains positive in view of the potential represented by OSE's entire pipeline.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: EDENRED  :  AlphaValue maintains its 'sell' rating on the stock
full_text: AlphaValue confirms its 'sell' rating on EdenRed shares, with a six-month price target of 50.6 euros, suggesting a potential decline of nearly 14% from the current price.The analyst reports that EdenRed has announced the acquisition of Reward Gateway for 1.3 billion euros, with an agreement expected to be concluded 'in the next few days'. A major player in the UK and Australia, EdenRed is billed as 'a leading employee engagement platform', with some 4,000 customers and 8 million users. The structure is expected to generate sales and EBITDA of £95m and £45m respectively in 2023, estimates the analyst firm.The deal values Reward Gateway at an EV/EBITDA 2023E multiple of 20x (post run rate synergies), and is expected to be EPS accretive from 2024.According to AlphaValue, the agreement is expected to generate >10 ME annual synergies within two years, and over 50 ME in potential operating revenues within the next five years.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: UBS raises target for FMC to 43.50 euros - 'Neutral'
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Major Swiss bank UBS raised its price target for Fresenius Medical Care (FMC) to 43.50 euros from 38 euros, but left its rating at "neutral". The share price rose after the company's capital markets day in April, analyst Graham Doyle wrote in a research note presented Tuesday. He said management had "built a bridge" there, so to speak, to achieving the margin target set for 2025. While the first quarter of 2023 was encouraging, the dialysis specialist still has a lot of work to do, he added./bek/ajx  Publication of the original study: 15.05.2023 / 17:02 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 15.05.2023 / 17:02 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: OSE IMMUNO :  Invest Securities lowers its target
full_text: Invest Securities confirms its Buy rating on OSE Immunotherapeutics shares, with a price target lowered from 10.3 to 8.26 euros. The analyst reports that on Friday after trading, OSE Immuno announced that it had regained the rights to OSE-127 after Servier decided not to pursue development of this asset following the failure of phase IIa in Sjögren's syndrome.'As a reminder, in 2016, the two groups had entered into a collaboration to address autoimmune diseases with OSE-127 as part of 2 clinical trials conducted in parallel. Servier had placed a license option on OSE-127, which it has therefore decided not to exercise, thereby cancelling out the potential for an associated milestone of 15mE', says the analyst. Invest Securities has thus adjusted its model by withdrawing the Sjögren's syndrome program line, but remains positive in view of the potential represented by OSE's entire pipeline.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: UBS lowers target for Bayer to 96 euros - 'Buy'
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Major Swiss bank UBS cut its price target for Bayer to 96 euros from 100 euros and left its rating at "buy." The pharmaceutical and agrochemical group's stock last week saw one of the worst price reactions to quarterly results he has seen in about a decade, analyst Michael Leuchten wrote in a research note released Tuesday. While the first quarter was weak, he said, expectations were not high and the magnitude of the negative share price reaction surprised him. This could have been because investors feared falling consensus estimates and jeopardized corporate targets for the full year. However, he did not share this concern./edh/bek  Original study publication date: 05/15/2023 / 11:53 GMT. title: SHARES FLASH :  Ceconomy slumps - 'Investors probably expected more'
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Shares in Ceconomy fell sharply on Monday after the presentation of figures for the second fiscal quarter and the confirmed outlook for the full year 2022/23. In the afternoon, the securities of the electronics retailer lost 12.3 percent to 2.286 euros, which means that the strong recovery gain since the beginning of the year has melted down to around 23 percent. The papers also sank below not only the 21-day line, which indicates the short-term trend, but also below the supports signaling the medium-term trend.      Analyst Volker Bosse of Baader Bank commented on the sharp price losses: "The market probably expected more after the nearly six percent price gain on Friday." Investors were probably worried about management's comments on consumer sentiment and the challenging environment, even though CEO Karsten Wildberger had expressed confidence about the start to the second half of the year.      In his study on the stock, Bosse had expressed an overall positive view after the figures. With regard to the stationary business, he pointed out that Ceconomy had continued to recover from the pandemic. Adjusted operating profit had exceeded expectations, with improvements in Germany, but also in Turkey, offsetting the difficult market environment in Spain and Italy./ck/ngu

title: Varta stable at the lowest level since 2018 - figures weak as expected
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Shares of Varta have laboriously stabilized on Monday after the quarterly report at the lowest level since 2018. After a weaker start at 19.10 euros, the papers of the battery manufacturer turned slightly upward to 19.57 euros by midday. It remains an annual loss of 13 percent, after they had already slumped by 80 percent in the previous year.      On the high of the low targets, the group has closed the first quarter, said analyst Philipp Konig of Goldman Sachs. In the CoinPower division, with its lithium-ion button cells for wireless headsets, for example, there was no recovery in sight, he said. Apple, the main customer, has cut back demand significantly, he said. Varta is trying to counteract this with reduced capacities and, in the short term, also with short-time work, in order to keep costs in check./ag/jha/

title: DZ Bank raises fair value for KWS Saat to 76 euros - 'Buy'.
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - DZ Bank has raised its fair value for KWS Saat from 75 to 76 euros after detailed figures for the first nine months and left its rating at "buy". In a study presented on Friday, DZ Bank analyst Axel Herlinghaus raised his estimates for net sales, unadjusted earnings before interest and taxes (Ebit) and earnings per share for the fiscal year slightly and consequently also the fair value. He said the bourse had recently largely ignored the company's compelling performance. He attributed this to the fact that the capital market is currently reviewing its fundamental assessment of agricultural stocks after the "premium year 2022." title: METZLER :  Dic Asset depends on market environment for debt target - 'Hold'.
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - According to bank Metzler, it is unlikely to be possible for real estate company Dic Asset to reduce its debt to the desired level in 2023. However, this is important against the background of increased interest rates, wrote analyst Jochen Schmitt in a study available on Friday.      He therefore lowered his investment rating for the stock from "buy" to "hold." Looking at his new price target of 7.60 euros, he still sees room for improvement compared to the current share price of 6.35 euros, but he still cut it by almost 40 percent. Previously, the target had been 12.00 euros.      Dic Asset will have a hard time reducing its leverage ratio LTV - as targeted for this year - to below 50 percent, he wrote. While Dic did manage to reduce its LTV in March from 57.8 percent at the end of December to 57.3 percent now, he said, this was only due to the sale of a larger property.      Even if the ratio is likely to fall by a further two percentage points in the current second quarter due to the placement of own properties into a fund, Schmitt sees little chance of this happening. Rather, a slight decline in portfolio value due to falling property prices is likely to counteract this. His own estimate for Dic's LTV is around 52.5 percent for December.      Moreover, the current environment for disposals remains difficult and, all things considered, Dic Asset has now become "too dependent on market conditions" to meet its LTV target, he added.      Rated "Hold," Bankhaus Metzler expects the company's share price to remain broadly stable over the next 12 months./ck/tih/mis  Analyzing institute Metzler Capital Markets. title: SOPRA STERIA :  AlphaValue adopts a positive recommendation
full_text: AlphaValue announced on Thursday that it had upgraded its recommendation on Sopra Steria shares to 'buy' from 'low', with a target price raised from €189 to €252.In a research note, the research firm points out that the acquisitions of CS Group, Tobania and Ordina will change the dimension of the technology group, enabling it to increase its annual sales by more than 15%.In addition to this simple scope effect, the Paris-based consultancy points out that these operations will enable the company to increase its geographical positioning in the Netherlands and Belgium, while reducing its exposure to France and the UK, which has been very high until now."All these elements mean that a discount can no longer be justified on the basis of a comparison with the valuations of its peers", concludes AlphaValue.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: Oddo BHF has reiterated its 'outperform' recommendation on Crédit Agricole, with its price target raised from 13.3 to 13.6 euros, following the publication of a 'very good quarterly result' and the raising of its 2023 estimates for the bank.The Group has benefited from very good underlying operating momentum", says the analyst, for whom "the increase in CET1, above the Group's target (11.0%), will also give it room for further growth".Oddo BHF continues to believe that the very good business mix is poorly valued at the current share price, which represents 0.82 times tangible equity at the end of last March, whereas Crédit Agricole is targeting a RoTE 2025 of over 12%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: T-Share firm on Tradegate after strong first quarter
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Strong quarterly figures from Deutsche Telekom boosted the T-Share ahead of the market on Thursday. On the Tradegate trading platform, it went up by just over one percent to 25.48 euros compared to the Xetra close the previous day.       One trader praised the fact that the Bonn-based group's report was consistently better than expected, thanks in part to its German business. The fact that business in the domestic market was better than forecast was also highlighted positively by JPMorgan analyst Akhil Dattani.      The slightly raised outlook, on the other hand, should not come as a major surprise, the trader said, as it reflected the raised annual targets of U.S. subsidiary T-Mobile US. All in all, according to him, the quarterly report now has the potential to help the stock out of its correction mode.       The stock has been in correction mode since the beginning of April, after reaching its highest level since the summer of 2001 on April 5 at just over EUR 23./ck/stk----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: BAYER WEAK ON TRADEGATE - EXPERT :  'Pharmaceuticals division disappoints'
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Somewhat weaker-than-expected quarterly figures from Bayer as well as more cautious annual targets hurt the shares of the pharmaceutical and agrochemical company on Thursday. title: Sixt in demand again after two weak days and figures
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - After recently two weak trading days, investors grab on Thursday vorborslich at Sixt again. A satisfactory first quarter and good prospects for the year as a whole were seen by the market as reasons why the shares rose by 3.7 percent in Tradegate trading compared to the Xetra closing price. On Tuesday and Wednesday, they had lost up to 6.9 percent in total.      It became apparent that the car rental company is feeling cost pressure, but is able to push through high prices. According to Baader expert Christian Obst, demand remains strong in most car rental regions. He therefore mentioned positively that sales volume had been the biggest growth driver. He added that the market environment remains positive.       Obst also mentioned that the consensus for pre-tax profit this year was 480 million euros, slightly below the midpoint of the target range. Sixt confirmed its full-year forecast of a "significant" increase in revenue and pre-tax profit of between 430 and 550 million euros./tih/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Dürr continues slide after quarterly figures - low for the year
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Dürr shares continued their previous day's slide at an accelerated pace on Wednesday. In the afternoon, the papers of the plant manufacturer fell to their lowest level since November 2022 and fell below the 200-day line, which is considered a longer-term trend indicator.       Most recently, they were down 5.7 percent at 29.38 euros, making them the weakest stock in the MDax. So far this year, the share price has lost around 7 percent. title: CEMENTIR HOLDING  :  Q1 23: Pricing boosts profitability
full_text:
Q1 23: Pricing boosts profitability EARNINGS/SALES RELEASESCementir Holding announced a good set of results, in line with our expectations. Despite a decline in volume, the company managed to increase revenue in most segments due to higher average selling prices, while maintaining its margins thanks to its hedging policy and a presence in niche markets. EBITDA increased by 41% and the margin increased by 290bps.
The results and guidance for FY23 are in line with our expectations so we won’t be making significant changes to our model.FACT*Revenue: €414.8m (vs €362.3m in Q1 22)
*EBITDA: €81.2m (vs €60.7m in Q1 22)
*PBT: €63.9m (vs €42.4m in Q1 22)
*Outlook for the full year re-iteratedANALYSISCementir Holding has reported a good set of Q1 results, with a significant increase in revenue and EBITDA. Despite a decrease in volumes of cement, RMC and aggregates, the company managed to achieve a 14.5% increase in revenue and a 33.8% increase in EBITDA due to its successful implementation of price increases.
The higher EBITDA was primarily seen in key markets such as the Nordics and Baltics, as well as Belgium, which together accounted for 73% of the group’s EBITDA. This was due to the company’s careful management of energy costs, supported by a strong hedging policy. As a result, Cementir Holding reported an increase of 290 bps.
While energy costs have reached their peak in the last year, they have now stabilized at a level that is still higher than the average for the previous years. Consequently, we anticipate that prices will drop following the decline in energy costs. However, it is important to note that inflation might cause labor and financial costs to continue to rise this year.
Performance by division
The Nordic and Baltic region, which accounted for 40% of the total revenue, saw flat growth of 1.3% as a slight fall in volume was offset by price increases. Denmark experienced a mid-single digit drop in volumes, while Norway and Sweden both saw double-digit decreases in volume, driven by high inflation and increased interest rates affecting the residential sector and investments in public works. Despite these challenges, revenue in Denmark increased by 13.2% and EBITDA by 62%, while Norway and Sweden were more affected, with revenue decreasing by 20% and EBITDA by 84% YoY. Nevertheless, the margin still increased by 74 bps.
The Belgium and France segment posted a robust performance, with a 19% increase in revenue and a 33% increase in EBITDA, despite a decline in volume. This was mainly due to successful price increases that offset the volume decline. The EBITDA margin also saw a significant increase of 240 bps, thanks to the company’s efficient management of energy costs.
In North America, the US market experienced lower demand for volume in Texas and California due to competitive pressure from imports. Despite this, revenue increased by 2.7% thanks to price increases and a positive FX impact of 4.4%. However, EBITDA decreased by 18% due to higher operating costs, resulting in a decrease of 320 bps in the EBITDA margin.
In the Asia Pacific region, Cementir Holding experienced mixed results. In China, there was a 6% decline in revenue due to lower prices, despite a 3% increase in volumes, resulting in a 31% drop in EBITDA due to increased production costs. Meanwhile, in Malaysia, revenue decreased by 3.4% due to a significant decrease in exports, which was offset by positive demand in the local market. EBITDA increased by 19.5% due to higher selling prices and lower freight costs, which compensated for lower volumes and increased production costs.
Despite a decrease in export volume from Turkey, the company managed to achieve an impressive 82% increase in sales. This growth was driven by successful price increases and an increase in demand in the domestic market. EBITDA also saw a significant improvement, standing at €7.8m compared to €1.6m previously, resulting in a 640bp increase in the EBITDA margin.
In Egypt, revenue decreased by 12.8% primarily due to the negative impact of FX (79%). However, EBITDA increased by 34% due to the efficient management of production costs and an increase in selling prices, resulting in a 940bp increase in the margin.IMPACTDespite a very strong quarter, the management has taken a conservative stance due to uncertainty around the potential risks associated with upcoming elections in Turkey and a slowdown in demand in the Nordics. Nonetheless, it has confirmed its full-year revenue guidance of over €1.8bn, EBITDA in the range of €335-345m and a net cash position of ~€200m. We too have a similar view and, hence, we will stick to our current estimates with no upward revisions to our numbers.

title: Hochtief very firm at daily high after strong first quarter
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Strong first-quarter figures and confirmation of the profit target for the full year boosted Hochtief shares on Tuesday.       They rose 2.8 percent to 78.60 euros after the afternoon release, reaching their highest level so far in the day. However, the 21-day line for the short-term trend, currently at just below 79.20 euros, still lies like a lid on the paper.      The construction group reported a jump in profits for the first quarter. The North America and Asia-Pacific regions in particular, as well as the business of the Spanish highway operator Abertis, in which Hochtief holds around 20 percent, performed significantly better.       Thanks to a good order backlog, the company, which moved up from the SDax to the MDax on Wednesday, also confirmed its full-year target of a net profit of between 510 and 550 million euros, adjusted for special items./ck/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

full_text: On Tuesday, Berenberg renewed its buy recommendation on Gaztransport et Technigaz (GTT), while lowering its target price for the stock from €140 to €137.The analyst points out that last month, the specialist in the design of membrane containment systems for LNG shipping and storage confirmed its targets for the full 2023 financial year.The Group, it points out, expects sales growth to accelerate in the second half of the year, driven by the growing number of LNG vessels under construction.The intermediary adds that its order book, which stands at 289 units, provides the company with particularly high visibility, greatly enhanced by the flow of orders from Qatar by 2023/24.With regard to the Korean Supreme Court's rejection of its request for an appeal in the case of the separation of technology licenses, Berenberg cites a decision that is "not very favorable", but which it believes should have a "modest" impact, in line with the expectations of GTT's management team.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Goldman starts Deutsche Borse with 'Neutral' - Target 189 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - U.S. investment bank Goldman Sachs initiated its rating on Deutsche Borse securities with a "Neutral" rating at a target price of 189 euros. Over the past decade, Borsen operators have expanded their activities and become diversified service providers for the needs of customers in the financial markets, analyst Oliver Carruthers wrote in an industry report available Tuesday. This has resulted in an increasing shift from volume-based cyclical revenues to more stable, recurring revenues, he added. The London Stock Exchange (LSE), which remains rated "Buy," is best positioned in this regard, he said. In contrast, the more volume-dependent competitors Deutsche Borse and Euronext, which are included in the rating at "Neutral", are likely to struggle with declining volumes over the course of the year. In addition, the Frankfurt-based companies have already priced in the medium-term growth prospects from their own resources./gl/ag      Publication of the original study: 09.05.2023 / 03:42 / BST First disclosure of the original study: Date in study not specified / Time in study not specified / Time zone in study not specified----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Fresenius jump up - FMC firm after quarterly figures
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Positive quarterly surprises at Fresenius and its subsidiary FMC brought gains for the shares of both companies on Tuesday. In particular, the papers of the hospital operator and medical manufacturer Fresenius went up. The shares rose by 6.4 percent to 27.06 euros, topping the slightly weakening Dax index and reaching their highest level since February.      The shares of the dialysis provider from the MDax, FMC, gained 1.3 percent to 43.16 euros. They were thus also among the favorites in the mid-cap index.      At Fresenius, quarterly sales rose slightly, while operating earnings adjusted for special effects fell far less than analysts had feared. FMC's operating profit was also better than expected, as Jefferies analyst James Vane-Tempest pointed out. However, Bernstein analyst Lisa Bedell Clive cautioned, expectations for the bloodwashing specialist had also been very low. The expert was not surprised by the lack of a major jump in the FMC share price after the figures after the recent good run - since the turn of the year, the price has gained a good 40 percent.       However, the better-than-expected sales and the strong quarterly operating result of the U.S. competitor DaVita from the previous evening, which also raised its annual targets, could have had a supporting effect on FMC.      Jefferies expert Vane-Tempest highlighted in particular the infusion division Kabi, which had been strong. According to him, the subsidiary Vamed was the reason why the annual targets were not raised in the first quarter, as Fresenius had initiated extensive restructuring measures at the hospital services provider.      Analyst Victoria Lambert of private bank Berenberg also praised the encouraging first quarter for Fresenius' core business segments. Kabi's margin, for example, was again within the target range set by management. The Helios hospital division performed as expected and FMC better than expected. The fact that Vamed had again made losses had also been sufficiently communicated in advance./ck/tav/stk

title: Wacker Neuson suffers from profit-taking
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - After a share price increase of around 80 percent since the end of September, investors are cashing in on Wacker Neuson on Tuesday. Shares recently fell three percent following the construction equipment manufacturer's quarterly report, after trading above the 23-euro mark for the first time in more than a year in the days before. The recently clearly rising 21-day line was thus not yet in danger.      According to initial voices, there was no criticism of the results. According to expert Martin Comtesse of Jefferies Research, the company had a strong start to the year - with growth and profitability both better than this year's target range.      "Although component availability has improved significantly, logistics still faces daily challenges. However, the situation should continue to improve in the coming months," the Jefferies expert wrote. The strongest momentum continues to come from North America, where Wacker continues to expand its connected dealer network./tih/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: BAADER :  Rational valuation now too demanding in interest rate environment
full_text: MUNICH (dpa-AFX) - Baader Bank considers the shares of Rational no longer attractively valued after their recent good run. As a result of a recovery in the share price of up to 75 percent since September 2022, analyst Peter Rothenaicher downgraded the shares of the catering equipment manufacturer from "Add" to "Reduce", even though he raised the price target from 590 to 635 euros. Compared with the current price of 694 euros, this implies a downside potential of 8.5 percent.      Rothenaicher has no doubts about Rational's long-term growth prospects in his study, which was published after the close of business on Friday. The expert attributed the current valuation of the shares, which in his view is too high, to the current interest rate environment. At 7.25 percent, he included a higher weighted average cost of capital in his model.      In comparison with the last ten years, the price-earnings ratio (P/E ratio) of the securities is not high, the expert noted. However, this should be seen in the light of the fact that, unlike now, these years were characterized by extremely low interest rates. In view of a key interest rate of the European Central Bank (ECB) of 3.75 percent, he considers the P/E ratio "very high".      Operationally, however, the analyst continues to see Rational on a good path. He considers the recently presented quarterly figures to be strong and the medium-term outlook to be favorable. Within five to ten years, the company could probably grow annually in the high single-digit percentage range. In the medium term, he believes it is possible for the operating margin to reach slightly above 25 percent on a sustainable basis.      With a "Reduce" rating, Baader Bank expects a total return (calculated from share price increase and dividend) of -10 to +5 percent for the share over the next 12 months./tih/edh/mis      Analyzing institute Baader Bank. title: AIR FRANCE :  Stifel upgrades its opinion on the stock
full_text: Stifel upgrades Air France shares to Buy with a price target of 2.20E.A decision taken to reflect the improvement in Stifel's opinion on the sector ' thanks to a better structural outlook for supply and demand and the resulting improvement in earnings estimates ', says the analyst.' At the same time, pressure on Air France-KLM's balance sheet has eased with the new legislation in France, and the stock is trading on a low valuation (~30% discount to peers based on 2024 EV/EBITDA) ', notes Stifel again.The outlook and trends are positive for the rest of the year, notes the broker, who points out that although no EBIT forecast has been provided at this stage, Stifel expects to achieve "2.0 billion euros, well above the consensus of 1.5 billion euros".Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: L'ORÉAL :  Bernstein downgrades its opinion
full_text: On Thursday, Berstein's analysts downgraded their opinion on L'Oréal shares from "outperform" to "perform in line with the market", with a price target raised from 400 to 445 euros.In a sector note, the research firm justifies its decision by pointing to the 31.5% rise in the share price since the start of the year, which it believes has brought it close to the valuation model it has established for the stock. More generally, Bernstein believes that the European FMCG sector is currently overvalued by up to 10%, while the economic outlook shows no potential for recovery.According to the analysts, L'Oréal remains one of the best companies in the sector, and one of the strategic stocks to hold alongside Beiersdorf, Lindt and Nestlé, but they feel they are not in a position to recommend that investors increase their positions further in the current environment.While they recognize that the group's organic growth could still surprise on the upside (+13% in the first quarter, and without the help of China), the professionals also judge that the stock remains vulnerable to a possible surge in bond yields.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Warburg Research downgrades Deutsche Post to 'Hold' - Target 47 euros
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Analysts Warburg Research downgraded Deutsche Post from "buy" to "hold," but raised its price target from 46 to 47 euros. The risk/reward ratio of Deutsche Post is becoming less and less attractive, analyst Christian Cohrs justified his new investment recommendation in a study published on Thursday. Therefore, he is now more cautious with regard to the further share price development, although he is positive about the general quality and financial prospects of the logistics group. Due to the good figures for the first quarter, however, he had slightly raised his forecasts./edh/la  Publication of the original study: 04.05.2023 / 08:15 / CEST First disclosure of original study: Date not stated in study / Time not stated in study / CEST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: BNP PARIBAS :  Oddo BHF raises its price target
full_text: Oddo BHF reiterates its 'outperform' recommendation on BNP Paribas, with a price target raised from 75 to 77 euros "to take into account the good revenue momentum", which leads it to raise its EPS forecasts.The research firm points to a 5.3% rise in underlying revenues for the bank in the first quarter, with a low cost of risk and the group's forecast of a significant increase in its distributable net income.Oddo BHF also highlights a balance sheet that 'remains extremely solid', and points out that the stock 'is still trading at very low multiples (around 0.66 times tangible equity for a RoTE 2025 of around 12%)'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Bernstein downgrades Beiersdorf to 'Market-Perform' - Target 130 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. analyst firm Bernstein Research downgraded Beiersdorf from "outperform" to "market perform," but raised its price target from 120 to 130 euros. Analyst Bruno Monteyne justified his new investment recommendation with the good share price performance and the 10 percent too high valuation of the consumer goods sector. Consumer spending remains high, but this is already priced into the sector, he wrote in an industry report published on Thursday./edh/la  Original study publication date: 03.05.2023 / 21:18 / UTC First disclosure of the original study: 04.05.2023 / 04:00 / UTC----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Rheinmetall with setback after mixed results
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - A mixed quarterly report and a confirmed forecast did not satisfy Rheinmetall investors, who had become accustomed to share price increases in recent months, on Thursday.       In Tradegate trading, it went down by 3.6 percent compared to the Xetra closing price after the operating result did not meet expectations. Driven by rising defense spending, the stock has been the best-performing Dax stock this year, rising more than 40 percent.      According to expert George McWhirter of Berenberg Bank, first-quarter sales exceeded expectations, but operating profit and free cash flow did not.       Above all, cash flow and the lack of a target increase should weigh on the share price at the start on Thursday, he expressed his suspicions. While the consensus is already slightly above the year-to-date targets, Rheinmetall is sticking to them./tih/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: DASSAULT SYSTÈMES :  Oddo BHF maintains its opinion
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform recommendation on Dassault Systèmes shares and keeps its price target at 47E.' DSY's performance is mixed ytd both because of weaker commercial momentum in the short term and because the market fears that the group will carry out a transforming operation', notes the analyst.As a result of this underperformance, the stock is now trading at ' 23x EV/EBITA 2024, a discount of over 20% to its PLM software peers (c. 30x)'.For Oddo BHF, the share's weakness is 'a buying opportunity, as operating momentum should clearly improve from the second quarter onwards (the recovery in China alone justifies an acceleration of +1pt) and as we understand that there are no M&A operations planned in the short term'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Lacroix: share price rises, analyst in support
full_text: Lacroix shares rose by almost 3% on the Paris Bourse on Wednesday, as analysts at Portzamparc added the company to their list of "High Five" mid-cap stocks.The brokerage firm has issued a buy recommendation on the stock, together with a price target of 46.6 euros, representing a potential upside of 53%.In its study, Portzamparc explains that it sees "numerous catalysts" for the stock, judging in particular that the potential linked to the proposed disposal of the signalling activities has not been well integrated by the market.The intermediary also expects "good" first-quarter sales to be published on May 9.Lacroix manufactures electronic equipment for its customers, as well as IoT and AI solutions for the automotive, industrial, connected homes and buildings, aerospace/defense and healthcare sectors.The company also provides connected and secure equipment and solutions to optimize critical smart road infrastructures (public lighting, traffic management) as well as water and energy infrastructures.In addition to Lacroix, Portzamparc's 'High Five' list includes Akwel, Equasens, Spie and Trigano.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: CRÉDIT AGRICOLE :  Oddo BHF positive ahead of quarterly results
full_text: Oddo BHF is reiterating its 'outperform' recommendation on Crédit Agricole, with the price target maintained at 13.3 euros, ahead of the banking group's publication of its results for the first quarter of 2023 on May 10.The research firm anticipates a slight decline in revenues, impacted by the switch to IFRS 17, but believes that the cost of risk should remain under control. title: Goldman raises target for Nemetschek to 70 euros - 'Neutral'
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. investment bank Goldman Sachs raised its price target for Nemetschek from 62 to 70 euros after quarterly results, but left its rating at "neutral." The construction software maker performed better than expected as customers brought forward purchases due to expected price increases, analyst Mohammed Moawalla wrote in a research note presented Wednesday. title: Investors speculate on bidding war for Software AG
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - The prospect of a bidding war for Software AG drove the share price on Tuesday to its highest level since June 2022. At last count, the shares were up by more than seven percent to a good 33 euros. This put them in second place in the SDax small caps index - behind the shares of SGL Carbon, which jumped even higher following a buy recommendation from Deutsche Bank.      There may be a duel in the takeover of Software AG. Almost two weeks ago, the technology investor Silver Lake had offered 30 euros per share for a purchase of the software developer. Over the weekend, financial investor Bain Capital surprisingly announced an indirect stake of a good 10 percent in the Darmstadt-based company. The Bloomberg news agency reported that Bain is seeking talks with Software AG regarding a possible merger with its portfolio company Rocket Software.      On Monday of last week, Silver Lake's purchase offer sent the Software share price shooting up by around 50 percent to the 30 euros per share offered by the prospective buyer. But the stock market quickly seemed to be betting on more: On Thursday and Friday, the shares gained a further four percent to 30.90 euros. On Friday, Silver Lake announced that it had purchased a further five percent of the software provider. The company had thus secured a total stake of more than 30 percent. Furthermore, the Software AG Foundation cannot withdraw from the purchase agreement for 25.1 percent of the shares, Silver Lake said - the agreement is also not dependent on reaching the minimum acceptance threshold. Ultimately, Software AG is to be delisted from the stock exchange.      "Even higher interest rates have not stopped Silver Lake (...) from taking on debt for the intended takeover of Software AG (...)," wrote analyst Chandramouli Sriraman of investment house Stifel. The topic of M&A - mergers and acquisitions - had returned to the European software industry. Cloud providers are currently proving resilient, said the expert, who referred in this context to recent high revenue growth of industry giants Microsoft and Amazon in the US. Software AG is currently rebuilding its business in the direction of subscription revenues and also intends to offer more cloud software.      The purchase price of 30 euros offered by Silver Lake represents a premium of 48 percent on the weighted average price of the past three months in terms of stock market volume, Sriraman said. The bid values the shares at almost 23 times the company's expected earnings per share for the current year. If the earnings forecast for 2024 were used as a yardstick, the premium offered to shareholders would still be just under 20 times.      Analyst Charles Brennan from US broker Jefferies also referred to a sector-specific aspect of Silver Lake's purchase offer for Software AG. While the former stock market darlings from the semiconductor industry are now struggling, investors are now turning to the software industry as a hoped-for "safe haven" in the technology sector. The trend toward acquisitions of medium-sized European software providers is likely to continue, Brennan suspects./bek/men/stk

title: DEUTSCHE BANK :  SGL restructuring is paying off
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Carbon specialist SGL Carbon should gradually reap the rewards of its restructuring, according to Deutsche Bank. Analyst Lars Vom-Cleff upgraded the shares, which are listed in the small-cap index SDax, from "hold" to "buy" with a price target raised from 9.30 to 13.00 euros. This was stated in a study published on Tuesday.      Vom-Cleff considers the company's 2023 forecast for operating earnings (Ebitda) to be conservative, and the targeted sales merely at a stable level also calls for explanation. The expert raised his estimates for Ebitda in 2023 and 2024 by 15 and 16 percent, respectively. He takes into account the company's targets until 2027 and pointed out that SGL aims to increase profitability faster than sales. In the first quarter, the successful development of the previous year should have continued.      The medium-term outlook is ambitious, but nevertheless achievable. This underlines that SGL is in the process of switching from restructuring to growth mode. Free cash flow and key balance sheet ratios have improved significantly since the start of the latest restructuring program, Vom-Cleff added. He said 2023 will likely still be a year of investment and stabilization, but from next year on, all four of SGL's divisions should again demonstrate sales and earnings growth.      With a Buy rating, Deutsche Bank recommends buying the stock based on the expected total return for the next twelve months.  Analyzing institute Deutsche Bank./ajx/ag/tih  Publication of the original study: 02.05.2023 / Time not specified in study / CET  First disclosure of the original study: 02.05.2023 / 06:48 / CET

title: ERAMET  :  Oddo BHF remains positive with lowered target
full_text: Oddo BHF confirms its 'outperform' rating on Eramet, but lowers its target price from €140 to €137, a 'relatively modest' adjustment given that its price assumptions are broadly unchanged, as are its volume assumptions beyond 2023.  Despite a less buoyant momentum, Eramet still benefits from an attractive valuation, with a discount of more than 50% to 2024-25 EBITDA multiples in the sector, while the improvement in the operating profile is on track", the analyst believes.Indeed, he points to the exit from the alloys business, which should be completed in June with the sale of Erasteel, and the start-up in early 2024 of the Centenario lithium project in Argentina, whose contribution should rise to a third of EBITDA by 2026.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: UBS lowers target for Sartorius to 500 euros - 'Buy'.
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - The major Swiss bank UBS lowered its price target for Sartorius from 508 to 500 euros, but left its rating at "buy." Measured on the basis of the price/earnings ratio in relation to the expected long-term earnings growth, the shares of the pharmaceutical and laboratory equipment provider appear too undervalued, analyst Michael Leuchten wrote in a study published Tuesday. Trends in the global market for biopharmaceutical production processes are on the company's side, he said. The lower price target is based on an update of his estimates after the latest quarterly figures.
